  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "His servants conspired against him and slew him in his palace; whereupon the people of the land, i.e., the population of Judah (הארץ עם  equals  יהוּדה עם,   ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 26:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), put the conspirators to death and made Josiah the son of Amon king, when he was only eight years old. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
